Mark a class as a BentoML service.

Example:

    @service(traffic={"timeout": 60})
    class InferenceService:
        @api
        def predict(self, input: str) -> str:
            return input

Sets all the headers in `other` in this object.

For example, if this object is `{"my-header": "my-value", "my-other-header": "my-other-value"}`
and other is {"my-header": 3¸ "other-header": 4}

The monitor implementation to log data to OTLP endpoint.
The otlp exporter could be configured by environment variables or
by passing arguments to the monitor from the config file.
For more information, please refer to:
\* <https://opentelemetry.io/docs/concepts/sdk-configuration/otlp-exporter-configuration/>

